<TITLE> One slaughtered in own courtyard </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gaibandha, Apr 20 9bdnews24.com)  Criminals slaughtered one Hazrat Ali, 55, at Dublagari village of Gobindaganj upazila in Gaibandha on Monday night. Fazlul Karim, OC of Gobindaganj Police Station told bdnews24.com that Hazrat Ali had been sleeping out in the courtyard due to the heat. Criminals killed him in the middle of the night. But the reason could not be ascertained. OC said that his wife had found him slaughtered when she came to call him. The neighbours rushed to the spot hearing her cries and informed the police of the matter. The police recovered the body and sent it to Gaibandha Sadr Hospital for post-mortem. A case has been filed with the Gobindaganj Police Station. bdnews24.
